      "text": "copy file \u0027../../Simple/.build/start.test.pr\u0027 to \u0027start-eq.txt\u0027, overwrite",
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Drift case 2 \u2014 the load-bearing reason this branch exists.\n\nStep text \u0060- assert %message% equals \u0027hello plang\u0027\u0060 (Tests/Simple/Start.goal:6)\ncarries no custom error message. With os/system/modules/assert/module.notes.md\nsaying \u0022omit Message from parameters and from formal unless the step text names\na custom error message; Expected is taken from the step text literal\u0022, the LLM\nshould emit:\nparameters: { Expected: \u0027hello plang\u0027, Actual: %message% }   (no Message key)\n\nPre-fix shape this test forbids:\nany Message parameter on assert.equals (when step text had no custom message)\n\nRead .pr requires copying to a .txt first because \u0027.pr\u0027 MIME deserializes to a\nGoal object, defeating substring assertions. Copy \u2192 read as text \u2192 assert.\nCompanion C# tests in DriftCaseArtifactTests.cs do the structural check too.\n\nArchitect\u0027s 3-fresh-cache rule runs externally (see sibling drift case).",
